AL-WIJAM DISEASE, DATE PALM - EGYPT (02): CLARIFICATION
*******************************************************

A ProMED-mail post
http://www.promedmail.org
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
http://www.isid.org

Date: 31 May 2011
From: Hayam Abdelkader <hayamabdelkader68@yahoo.com>


Re: Al-Wijam disease, date palm - Egypt: 1st report 20110519.1512
-----------------------------------------------------------------

Based on the preliminary results of our study, the occurrence of Al

Wijam disease in date palm of Egypt cannot be conclusively verified.

This is because we could not detect the causal agent by electron
microscopy in affected plants. Moreover, no DNA sequencing has been

performed yet to support the occurrence of Al Wijam disease in
Egypt.

Thank you for posting this follow-up as a clarification.

--
Dr. Hayam Abdelkader
Associate Professor
Faculty of Science, Biotechnology Department
Taif University
Saudi Arabia
<hayamabdelkader68@yahoo.com>

[We are happy to disseminate this statement of clarification by one

of the co-authors of the cited paper:

